Class Animal

java.lang.Object
animals.Animal
All Implemented Interfaces:
itumulator.executable.DynamicDisplayInformationProvider, itumulator.simulator.Actor
Direct Known Subclasses:
Bear, Rabbit, Wolf
public abstract class Animal extends Object implements itumulator.simulator.Actor, itumulator.executable.DynamicDisplayInformationProvider
The Animal class represents the base class for all animal entities in the simulation. It provides shared properties and behaviors, such as movement, growth, breeding, energy management, and interactions with nests and other entities.

Subclasses of Animal are expected to implement behaviors by overriding abstract methods such as dayTimeAI(), nightTimeAI(), and generalAI().
